{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8d0-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10513"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10513"},"text":"§ 10513.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Application requirements","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"No grant may be made under this subchapter unless an application has been submitted to the Attorney General in which the applicant certifies that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8d1-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10513/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" DNA analyses performed at the laboratory will satisfy or exceed then current standards for a quality assurance program for DNA analysis issued by the Director of the Federal Bureau of Investigation under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s12591"},"text":"section 12591 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002048"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002048"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. The period probably should be a semicolon."}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8d2-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10513/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" DNA samples obtained by and DNA analyses performed at the laboratory shall be made available only—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8d3-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10513/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to criminal justice agencies for law enforcement identification purposes;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8d4-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10513/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in judicial proceedings, if otherwise admissible pursuant to applicable statutes or rules;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8d5-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10513/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" for criminal defense purposes, to a defendant, who shall have access to samples and analyses performed in connection with the case in which the defendant is charged; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8d6-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10513/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" if personally identifiable information is removed, for a population statistics database, for identification research and protocol development purposes, or for quality control purposes; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8d7-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10513/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the laboratory and each analyst performing DNA analyses at the laboratory shall undergo semiannual external proficiency testing by a DNA proficiency testing program that meets the standards issued under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s12591"},"text":"section 12591 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8d8-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/351/tI/s2403"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–351, title I, § 2403","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322/tXXI/s210302/c/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322, title XXI, § 210302(c)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2066"},"text":"108 Stat. 2066","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/546/s8/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–546, § 8(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/2735"},"text":"114 Stat. 2735","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id4ccba8d9-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id4ccba8da-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id4ccba8db-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3796kk–2"},"text":"section 3796kk–2 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id4ccba8dc-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/546"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–546","children":[],"tail":" substituted “semiannual” for “, at regular intervals not exceeding 180 days,”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
